                        "content": "The client tells the nurse they cannot leave home without checking numerous times that \"everything electrical has been shut off.\" The client's statement supports which mental health diagnosis?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nA repetitive behavior that interferes with activities of daily living and functioning is indicative of obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD). This repetitive behavior is not associated with phobias, generalized anxiety disorder, or post-traumatic stress disorder.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Recognize Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Anxiety, Mood and Affect\nStrategies: Data in the Question, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, behaviors in OCD, and note the data in the question. Recalling that repetitive behavior is indicative of OCD and noting the relationship between the client behaviors described in the question and the name of the disorder will direct you to the correct option.\n ",
                        "id": "6abaecc7655743db82cd0fac1018395a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
