                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is preparing to create a care plan for a client admitted to the mental health unit with a diagnosis of obsessive-compulsive disorder. The nurse would plan to include which component as a priority in the plan of care?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "49d86bb4d5071eb7de614d6c79f7abfb",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Creating创新",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe priority would be to develop individualized goals and objectives in the plan of care. Goals and objectives are a mutual working tool between the client and the nurse. Although the medical diagnosis of the client is considered in planning care, it is not specifically a component of a nursing care plan. Attendance at group therapy sessions and promotion of self-care measures may be components of the plan of care, but these interventions would follow after development of the goals and objectives.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Creating\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Care Coordination\nStrategies: Steps of the Nursing Process, Strategic Words\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, priority. Option 1 can be eliminated first because it is not necessarily a specific component of the nursing care plan. Regarding the remaining options, use the steps of the nursing process as a guide to assist in directing you to the correct option. The correct option identifies planning. Developing goals and objectives would be done before developing interventions.\n ",
                        "id": "e814490777164c998e7d846a339a365a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c4641e93edc1424092ad2b9b81dca30a",
                                "content": "Monitor for repetitive behavior."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1afef7193054412b8d3428ef9b67c020",
                                "content": "Demand active participation in care."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c5daa6091923483a99dd5c745422120f",
                                "content": "Educate the client about self-care needs."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f1b744fd398248a88023ec82ca645f1d",
                                "content": "Establish a trusting nurse-client relationship."
                            }
                        ],
