                        "content": "The nurse is developing a plan of care for a client admitted to the mental health unit with a diagnosis of obsessive-compulsive disorder. What is the nurse's priority in the plan of care?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe priority is to establish a trusting relationship with the client. Demanding anything from the client would never occur. The remaining options are appropriate components of the plan of care but are not the priority. A trusting nurse-client relationship needs to be established first.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Prioritize Hypotheses\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Anxiety, Caregiving\nStrategies: Strategic Words, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the strategic word, priority. Note that the client is being admitted to the mental health unit. Focus on the subject, planning of care for a client with obsessive-compulsive disorder. Recalling that the nurse-client relationship needs to be developed first will assist in directing you to the correct option.\n ",
